  <text>
    <body>
      <div type="letter" xml:id="cassatt-to-beatty-1909">
        <opener>
          <dateline>
            <note>1746(unknown information)</note>
            <date when="1909-10-06">Oct 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date>
            <address>
              <placeName ref="#Fra">
                <region><lb/>Mesnil-Beaufresne</region>
                <region><lb/>Fresneaux-Montchevreuil</region>
                <region><lb/>Mesnil-Théribus (Oise)</region>
                <note>The Château de Beaufresne, dating from the late 18th century, was purchased by the American artist Mary Cassatt in 1894, who modernized it with amenities like central heating and electricity. She lived there until her death in 1926, using the restored mill on the property as her engraving studio. Deeply involved in the local village life, Cassatt supported the community, especially children. The château previously belonged to Admiral de Grasse, a key figure in the American War of Independence, and was later inherited by Cassatt’s niece, who donated it to a family services association.</note>
              </placeName>
            </address>
          </dateline>
          <salute>My Dear <persName ref="#Beatty">Mr. Beatty</persName></salute>
        </opener>
        <p>
          <lb/>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;In reply to your favor 
          <lb/>of <date when="1909-09-16">Sept. 16<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> asking for my phot
          <lb/>ograph, I will forward one, 
          <lb/>though it would be very<seg type="feeling" ana="#discomfort"> disagreeable</seg>
          <lb/>to me to have my image in a 
          <lb/>catalogue or in any publication.
        </p>
        <p>
          <lb/>&#160;It is always<seg type="feeling" ana="#discomfort"> unpleasant</seg> to me
          <lb/>to see the photograph of the 
          <lb/>artist accompany their work, that
          <lb/>has the further tie or with the 
          <lb/>personal appearance of the author
          <lb/>of picture or statue. <q>Why should 
          <lb/>such curiosity—if it exists—be 
          <lb/><seg type="feeling" ana="#gratified">gratified</seg>?</q>
        </p>
        <closer>
          <seg type="feeling" ana="#regret">With regrets I send.</seg>
          <salute>Regards. Believe me</salute>
          <signed><persName ref="#Cassatt">Mary Cassatt</persName></signed>
        </closer>
      </div>
    </body>
